<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900709-0046</DOCNO><DOCID>900709-0046.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- CMS Energy Corp.:   Curbs Lifted on Firm's Use   Of Debt, Equity in Plant</HL><DATE>07/09/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11</SO><CO>   CMS</CO><GV>JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)</GV><LP>   CMS Energy Corp. said a Michigan circuit court judgeremoved restrictions on the company's use of its $1.5 billionof debt and equity interests in the Midland CogenerationVenture.   But the court said that CMS's Consumer's Power Co. utilityunit must maintain a $450 million corporate bond, as orderedearlier by Michigan regulators.</LP><TEXT>   In its ruling, the court removed all restrictions on theuse by Dearborn, Mich.-based CMS of the $1.2 billion in notesand $300 million in equity it received in return for itscontribution to the cogeneration venture. The venture is a1,380-megawatt power plant converted from CMS's failed effortto build a nuclear plant in Midland.   The court action also relieved CMS of having to file a$100 million surety bond previously required by anothercourt.   CMS said the decision will become effective Aug. 3, andthe company isn't planning an appeal.</TEXT></DOC>